<th>
<h2><span id="Mario_&amp;_Nintendo_news"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Mario_.26_Nintendo_news">Mario &amp; Nintendo news</span></h2>
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td>
<div style="padding:0 8px 1px 0;margin-top:-1px">
<div><div class="mainpage-image-wrapper" style="float:right;clear:right;background:#fff;--darkbg:#222;border:1px solid #3B587E;margin:0 0 0.2em 0.7em">
<a href="/File:TSMGM_UHDBR_US.jpg" class="image"><img alt="US Ultra HD Blu-ray cover for The Super Mario Galaxy Movie" src="https://mario.wiki.gallery/images/thumb/7/77/TSMGM_UHDBR_US.jpg/130px-TSMGM_UHDBR_US.jpg" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="130" height="166" srcset="https://mario.wiki.gallery/images/thumb/7/77/TSMGM_UHDBR_US.jpg/195px-TSMGM_UHDBR_US.jpg 1.5x, https://mario.wiki.gallery/images/thumb/7/77/TSMGM_UHDBR_US.jpg/260px-TSMGM_UHDBR_US.jpg 2x" data-file-width="1177" data-file-height="1500" /></a></div>
<ul><li><i><b><a href="/The_Super_Mario_Galaxy_Movie" title="The Super Mario Galaxy Movie">The Super Mario Galaxy Movie</a></b></i> was released on <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DVD" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:DVD">DVD</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blu-ray" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:Blu-ray">Blu-ray</a>, and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ultra_HD_Blu-ray" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:Ultra HD Blu-ray">Ultra HD Blu-ray</a> <i>(pictured)</i> in the United States on June 16, 2026.</li>
<li>The <a href="/Mario_Kart_World_(Nintendo_Music)" title="Mario Kart World (Nintendo Music)">15 music tracks</a> from <i><b><a href="/Mario_Kart_World" title="Mario Kart World">Mario Kart World</a></b></i> that arrange music from <i><a href="/Super_Mario_Bros." title="Super Mario Bros.">Super Mario Bros.</a></i>, <i><a href="/Super_Mario_Bros._2" title="Super Mario Bros. 2">Super Mario Bros. 2</a></i>, and <i><a href="/Super_Mario_Bros._3" title="Super Mario Bros. 3">Super Mario Bros. 3</a></i> were made available on the <a href="/Nintendo_Music" title="Nintendo Music">Nintendo Music</a> app on June 15, 2026.</li>
<li>In the <a target="_blank" rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PvUPDSDZg1k">Nintendo Direct</a> for June 2026, the limited-time <a href="/Nintendo_Switch_Online" title="Nintendo Switch Online">Nintendo Switch Online</a> <b><a href="/DK_Challenge" title="DK Challenge">DK Challenge</a></b> Event was announced for <a href="/Nintendo_Switch_2" title="Nintendo Switch 2">Nintendo Switch 2</a>, taking place from June 9 to September 1. Additionally, a <i><a href="/Super_Mario_(franchise)" title="Super Mario (franchise)">Super Mario</a></i> collaboration event was announced for <i><b><a href="/Donkey_Kong_Bananza:_DK_Island_%26_Emerald_Rush" title="Donkey Kong Bananza: DK Island &amp; Emerald Rush">Donkey Kong Bananza: DK Island &amp; Emerald Rush</a></b></i> for the <a href="/Super_Mario_Bros._40th_Anniversary" title="Super Mario Bros. 40th Anniversary">Super Mario Bros. 40th Anniversary</a>, with the first wave to take place from June 9 to June 30. A <i><a href="/Donkey_Kong_Bananza" title="Donkey Kong Bananza">Donkey Kong Bananza</a></i>–themed alarm was also added to <b><a href="/Nintendo_Sound_Clock:_Alarmo" title="Nintendo Sound Clock: Alarmo">Nintendo Sound Clock: Alarmo</a></b> on the same day.</li>
<li>The 18 music tracks from <i><b>Mario Kart World</b></i> that arrange music from <i><a href="/Super_Mario_Galaxy" title="Super Mario Galaxy">Super Mario Galaxy</a></i> and <i><a href="/Super_Mario_Galaxy_2" title="Super Mario Galaxy 2">Super Mario Galaxy 2</a></i> were made available on the Nintendo Music app on June 8, 2026.</li></ul></div>
</div>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<table id="dyk" class="mainpagebox">
<tbody><tr>
<th>
<h2><span id="Did_you_know?"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Did_you_know.3F">Did you know?</span></h2>
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td>
<div style="padding:0 8px 1px 0;margin-top:-2px">
<div><div class="mainpage-image-wrapper" style="float:right;clear:right;background:#fff;--darkbg:#222;border:1px solid #3B587E;margin:0 0 0.2em 0.7em">
<a href="/File:Super_Mario_64_Boxart.png" class="image"><img alt="North American box art of Super Mario 64." src="https://mario.wiki.gallery/images/thumb/3/3e/Super_Mario_64_Boxart.png/100px-Super_Mario_64_Boxart.png" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="100" height="70" srcset="https://mario.wiki.gallery/images/thumb/3/3e/Super_Mario_64_Boxart.png/150px-Super_Mario_64_Boxart.png 1.5x, https://mario.wiki.gallery/images/thumb/3/3e/Super_Mario_64_Boxart.png/200px-Super_Mario_64_Boxart.png 2x" data-file-width="1548" data-file-height="1080" /></a></div>
<ul><li>As the first 3D game of the <i><a href="/Super_Mario_(franchise)" title="Super Mario (franchise)">Super Mario</a></i> franchise and launch title for the <a href="/Nintendo_64" title="Nintendo 64">Nintendo 64</a>, <i><b><a href="/Super_Mario_64" title="Super Mario 64">Super Mario 64</a></b> (pictured)</i> has been widely acclaimed as one of the greatest and most important games of all time.</li>
<li>The musical theme  "<b><a href="/Dire,_Dire_Docks_(theme)" title="Dire, Dire Docks (theme)">Dire, Dire Docks</a></b>" has two additional versions that fade in depending on the player's location in the Aquatic levels.</li>
<li>The yellow rabbit, <b><a href="/MIPS" title="MIPS">MIPS</a></b>, is <a href="/Princess_Peach" title="Princess Peach">Princess Peach</a>'s pet <a href="/Rabbit" title="Rabbit">rabbit</a>.</li>
<li>In a poll created by Nintendo of Australia and New Zealand, the <b><a href="/Bob-omb_Battlefield" title="Bob-omb Battlefield">Bob-omb Battlefield</a></b> was voted the "#1 Best-Ever Sandbox-Style 3D Mario Stage".</li></ul></div>
</div>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
